data.name: tabControllerLibrary.SuperTooltip
data.value:
The Controller Library contains controllers that have been explicitly saved from the Scene Explorer.
You can drag and drop controllers from the library directly onto controllers in the Scene Explorer to replace them. You can also preview the controller's contents in the preview window of the library.

data.name: tabActors.SuperTooltip
data.value:
The Actor Library contains all the actors saved for a given workspace. You can drag and drop actors from the library directly onto a viewport. You can also preview the actor's contents in the preview window of the library.
When actors are dropped onto another actor, their components are added to the that actor. When actors are dropped onto a stage, an instance of the actor is created on the stage.

data.name: tabTextureLibrary.SuperTooltip
data.value:
The Texture Library shows the contents of the Texture Library folder in your workspace.
You can drag and drop textures from the library directly onto textures in the Texture Explorer to replace them. You can also preview the textures both in original and compressed forms in the preview window of the library.

data.name: tabMaterials.SuperTooltip
data.value:
The Material Library contains materials that have been explicitly saved from the Scene Explorer.
You can drag and drop materials from the library directly onto materials in the Scene Explorer to replace them. You can also preview the material's contents in the preview window of the library.

data.name: tabAudioLibrary.SuperTooltip
data.value:
The Audio Library shows the contents of the Audio Library folder in your workspace.
You can drag and drop audio from the library directly onto audio nodes in the Scene Explorer to replace them. You can also preview the audio in the preview window of the library.
